{"id":"5356","name":"for-real-this-time-pinkberry-coming-to-nashville-and-cool-springs","title":"For Real, This Time: Pinkberry Coming To Nashville, Cool Springs","author":"Morgan Levy","date":"2010-07-12T16:30:00-05:00","tags":["comings &amp; goings","cool springs pinkberry","froyo","frozen yogurt","nashville pinkberry","pinkberry","sweet cece&apos;s"],"categories":["Featured","Food &amp; Drink"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/roboppy/364198694/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"blank\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://farm1.static.flickr.com/143/364198694_836555a520.jpg\" alt=\"\"></a></p><p>On the local fro-yo front, Yogurt Oasis, Krave, Provence&#x2019;s Yummi-Yo!, Tasti D-Lite, Yogurt World Cafe, Menchie&#x2019;s and Sweet CeCe&#x2019;s aren&#x2019;t enough for the Nashville frozen yogurt elite, as we don&#x2019;t see a month or two pass by without hearing murmurs of the almighty <a href=\"http://www.pinkberry.com/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.pinkberry.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Pinkberry</a> coming to Nashville. And do we ever have good news for Pinkberry enthusiasts in Nashville&#x2026; Yes, the franchise is coming here, and they&#x2019;re bringing us double the frozen treats, with at least two stores in both Nashville and Cool Springs!</p><p>Nashville&#x2019;s new Pinkberry has finally made it out of the Google cache and on to <a href=\"http://www.pinkberry.com/storelocations.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.pinkberry.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Pinkberry.com</a> as a &#x201C;Swirling Soon&#x201D; store, and is <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=22133770663&amp;v=wall&amp;story_fbid=440606355663&amp;ref=mf\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.facebook.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">scheduled to open on October 1 at 2304 West End Ave</a> (the old Blockbuster location). Details are scarce for the Cool Springs store,&#xA0;<a href=\"http://nashville.craigslist.org/fbh/1830351553.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;nashville.craigslist.org&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">but they&#x2019;re hiring</a>! And it <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=22133770663&amp;v=wall&amp;story_fbid=430684265663&amp;ref=mf\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.facebook.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">sounds like</a> they have their sights set on locations in Green Hills and the Gulch, too.</p><p>Let&#x2019;s hear from you &#x2013; Are you excited that Pinkberry is opening in Nashville? Will you stick to your Sweet CeCe&#x2019;s, split your loyalties, or just start consuming twice as much yogurt (the obvious solution)?</p><p><em>Photo by </em><a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/roboppy/364198694/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\"><em>roboppy</em></a><em>. </em></p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2010/10/13/get-your-pinkberry-fix-west-end-grand-opening-thursday/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Get Your Pinkberry Fix: West End Grand Opening Thursday\">Get Your Pinkberry Fix: West End Grand Opening Thursday</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2008/10/22/krave-frozen-yogurt-were-getting-closer-to-pinkberry-every-day/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Krave Frozen Yogurt: We&#x2019;re Getting Closer To Pinkberry Every Day\">Krave Frozen Yogurt: We&#x2019;re Getting Closer To Pinkberry Every Day</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2009/07/28/tomorrow-tasti-d-lite-finally-opens-doors/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Tomorrow: Tasti D-Lite (Finally) Opens Doors\">Tomorrow: Tasti D-Lite (Finally) Opens Doors</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2009/11/04/clear-the-roads-cool-springs-chuys-open-for-business-and-heading-for-the-boro/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Clear The Roads, Cool Springs: Chuy&#x2019;s Open For Business (And Heading For The &#x2018;Boro)\">Clear The Roads, Cool Springs: Chuy&#x2019;s Open For Business (And Heading For The &#x2018;Boro)</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2008/08/01/cold-treats-tasti-d-lite-comes-to-town/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Cold Treats: Tasti D-Lite Comes To Town\">Cold Treats: Tasti D-Lite Comes To Town</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}